Data on the Ti–Sn–B phase equilibria are not available. The boundary binary phase diagrams were accepted from Massalski's handbook [4], where the Ti–B system is after [5] and Ti–Sn after [6] (Fig. 1
). Crystal structure data for the relevant binary phases are presented in Table 1
.

The ternary Ti–Sn–B system was studied in the region Ti–TiB–Ti3Sn using the alloys of 11 compositions in both as-cast and annealed states (Table 2
 and Fig. 2
). Annealing at 1450 or 1500°C for 4h was performed in a resistance furnace with a W heater in Ar gettered with Ti cuttings and subsolidus annealing was carried out in setting of pyrometric measurements of melting points after Pirani & Althertum under Ar at temperatures by 30–50°C below solidus for 1h just after the measurements. Cooling rates were estimated as ∼3 and ∼200°C/s, respectively.
